1.title: A Doc's Best Friend
1.plot: The clinic has gone to the dogs. There's an emergency visit from a great dane; a litter of puppies with tummy troubles; a jack russell who ate the wrong thing and a diabetic pinscher with a paw problem. All of this and a visit to Dr. Pol's staff and their canine companions.

2.title: Momma's Boy
2.plot: It's Mother's Day and Charles is planning a special surprise for Diane; however, Charles isn't the only one joining in the maternal good vibes. There are twin calves, a pregnant reindeer and a pregnant horse whose owner is also expecting.

3.title: Mind Your Business
3.plot: Charles is always scheming and looking for the next adventure, and this time he's settled on Bee keeping. WHile Charles is busy on the quest for artisan honey, the clinic is backed up with a hurt Husky, a miniature donkey named Fagan, and Mickers, a cat with a torn up ear.

4.title: Down on the Dairy
4.plot: A very special episode that looks at the farmers and farms that fuel Michigan's booming dairy business; however, it's still business as usual at the clinic when Gus, an injured shepherd, and Rico, a Hahns-Macaw, pay a visit.

7.title: Bridge Over the River Pol
7.plot: A simple bridge building project on the Pol homestead becomes an icy situation when Dr. Pol sinks the tractor into the frozen stream. The Pol's rally as a family to finish their bridge and create their own island paradise in the backyard.

8.title: Weather the Weather
8.plot: It's spring but instead of sunny days and flowers, Michigan is experiencing chilly weather and torrential showers. The soggy vets try to keep up good spirits amidst the rain and cold. Their patients, including a newborn reindeer who can't find his feet, are relying on them, come wind or rain, sleet or shine.

9.title: Dr. Mom
9.plot: The clinic is very excited and Dr. Emily is very pregnant. As the staff gets ready for the newest addition to the Pol Veterinary Family, it's business as usual with Ruby, a weimaraner in severe distress, an emergency at Stanley farm, and a special visitor at the clinic.

35.title: Finding Athena
35.plot: Valentine's Day has Charles longing for companionship, and after deliberation with his parents decides to get a Great Dane. Meanwhile at the clinic Dr Pol deals with a malnourished goose and Dr. Brenda has her hands full dehorning a litter of miniature goats.

36.title: Citizen Charles

14.title: Chasing Tom
14.plot: It's time to give thanks at Pol Veterinary Clinic, and this year there is so much to be thankful for; however, before the festivities can begin, Charles has an injured Tom and two turkey hens to capture. While Charles is adding turkey to the family, not the dinner plate, Dr. Pol helps two lucky families adopt some Great Danes in need.

15.title: North Pol
15.plot: Christmas has come to Michigan, but don't let the lack of a beard fool you, Dr. Pol is filled with the joy of the season and Charles, he's just filled with cookies. As Dr. Pol makes farm calls, Dr. Brenda comes to the aid of an amorous reindeer who is frantic to find amore

16.title: Night Before Christmas
16.plot: 'Twas the night before Christmas and all through the house, many creatures were stirring, it's a veterinary clinic after all. Christmas time has definitely arrived, but it's still business as usual, that is, until Santa shows up.
